President Uhuru Kenyatta and NASA principal Raila Odinga have mourned former Foreign Affairs Minister Munyua Waiyaki and 26 people who died in a road accident at Kambu on the Nairobi-Mombasa highway on Monday night.Uhuru described Waiyaki as an illustrious son of Kenya and a pioneer diplomat, who played a leading role in laying the foundation of the country&rsquo;s post-Independence development.&ldquo;As we mourn and pay homage to this visionary leader, let&rsquo;s also celebrate his life and achievements. Although Waiyaki has left us, his inspirational life will remain a great legacy to his family and the nation,&rdquo; he said. Waiyaki, 91, died yesterday morning while undergoing treatment at a Nairobi hospital.Raila said Waiyaki remains one of the most respected and successful Foreign ministers Kenya has had since Independence. &ldquo;He was responsible for building Kenya&rsquo;s image abroad in addition to crafting a clear foreign policy that clearly spelt out Kenya&rsquo;s terms of engagement with the international community,&rdquo; he said. They sent condolence messages to the families, relatives and friends of the 26 passengers who also perished.